## When to use
Use this skill when you need a quick overview of your disk space usage without diving into detailed reports.

## Approach
This skill leverages the `shell_exec` tool to run common Unix commands like `df -h`, which provides a human-readable summary of disk space usage. The output is then processed and displayed in a user-friendly format within KDEV.

## Example
```sh
result = shell_exec("df -h")
memory_write(result, "disk_summary.txt")
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that the `shell_exec` command has access to the necessary permissions to execute `df -h`. The output may vary based on the system's configuration and available disk partitions.